'''Adele Enersen''' is an author, illustrator,<ref>[https://www.pressreader.com/canada/toronto-star/20161108/281599535067745 "A Social Media Star before turning one"]. ''Toronto Star'', November 8, 2016, Kristen Thompson.</ref> [[screenwriter]], [[photographer]] and [[Blog|blogger]]<ref>[http://tulsabookreview.com/2012/03/when-my-baby-dreams/ "When My Baby Dreams"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418164820/http://tulsabookreview.com/2012/03/when-my-baby-dreams/ |date=April 18, 2015 }}. ''Tulsa Book Review''.</ref> originally from [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]].<ref name=tstar>[https://www.thestar.com/life/parent/2010/08/30/innovative_adventures_in_napping.html "Innovative adventures in napping"]. ''Toronto Star''</ref> She lives in [[Burbank, California]] with her husband, composer Lasse Enersen, and Vincent and Mila.<ref>[http://www.today.com/parents/vincent-night-mom-adele-enersen-draws-sleepless-baby-t15736 Today.com - Vincent and the Night]</ref>
Enersen created a blog, ''Mila's Daydreams'',<ref>[http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-06-207175-0 "When My Baby Dreams "]. ''Publishers Weekly''.</ref> where she posted photographs which she had taken of her baby daughter Mila in different costumes and props while she was asleep.<ref>Steven (29 September 2012). [http://en.rocketnews24.com/2012/09/29/japanese-babies-daydream-too-creative-infant-art-a-la-milas-daydreams-sweeps-japan/ "Japanese Babies Daydream Too! Creative Infant Art a la Mila’s Daydreams Sweeps Japan | RocketNews24"]. ''RocketNews24''.</ref><ref>[http://www.lifestyleetc.co.uk/2011/04/08/life-style-etcs-icy-heart-has-been-melted-by-adele-enersens-creative-use-of-her-sleeping-baby/ "Life.Style.etc’s icy heart has been melted by Adele Enersen’s creative use of her sleeping baby"]. ''Life.Style.etc.''.</ref> The blog attracted worldwide attention from writers on the subject of parenting.<ref name=tstar />
Enersen signed a publishing deal with [[HarperCollins]], and created two books, ''When My Baby Dreams'' and ''When My Baby Dreams Fairytales''.<ref>Worthington, Kate. [https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/adele-enersen/when-my-baby-dreams/ "When My Baby Dreams"]. ''Kirkus Reviews''.</ref><ref>[http://www.today.com/id/45816601/ns/today-today_books/t/tot-sleeps-baby-bookworm-surfer-astronaut-elephant-tamer/ "Sleeping like a baby, a bookworm and an astronaut"]. ''TODAY.com''.</ref> With her third book ''Vincent and the Night'', she signed a deal with [[Dial Pres]], [[Penguin Random House]]. The book was immediately listed "Best Book of the Month" Editor's pick in [[Amazon (company)|Amazon.com]].<ref>https://www.amazon.com/b/ref=chp_banner_BOTMPict?ie=UTF8&node=6258794011&pf_rd_m=ATVPDKIKX0DER&pf_rd_s=mobile-hybrid-1&pf_rd_r=0T9DPDDQNGZ7WQDXDBR8&pf_rd_t=30901&pf_rd_p=2053166842&pf_rd_i=6129451011 Amazon Book Of The Month</ref>
After the blog's popularity her books and illustrations were featured on international television news,<ref>ABC News. [http://abcnews.go.com/WNT/video/conversationthe-mom-milas-daydreams-11333965 "The Conversation:The Mom Behind 'Mila's Daydreams'"]. ''ABC News''.</ref> were reviewed in magazines and websites around the world,<ref>[http://www.bookilluminations.com/rev_when_my_baby_dreams.html "When My Baby Dreams"]. ''Book illuminations''.</ref> which in turn increased the readership of her blog.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/08/02/milas-daydreams-adorable_n_667477.html "Mila's Daydreams: Adorable Photos Imagine What Tots Dream About"]. ''The Huffington Post''. 2 August 2010.</ref>
